50|$|Usually, the <b>throttle</b> valve is <b>controlled</b> with a <b>throttle</b> pedal or lever via {{a direct}} {{mechanical}} linkage. In vehicles with electronic <b>throttle</b> <b>control,</b> the manual <b>throttle</b> <b>control</b> sends {{a signal to}} the Engine Control Unit (ECU), which then directly controls the position of the throttle valve. This means that the operator does not have direct <b>control</b> over the <b>throttle</b> valve; the ECU can finely control the valve in order to reduce emissions or maximize performance.|$|R
