50|$|Early cars {{such as the}} Ford Model T had a <b>hand</b> <b>lever</b> to <b>control</b> the <b>{{throttle}}.</b> Later cars {{used both}} a foot pedal and a <b>hand</b> <b>lever</b> to set the minimum throttle. This was an early form of cruise control. The 1918 Stutz Bearcat had a central throttle pedal with the clutch and brake {{to the right and}} left. Modern cruise control was invented in 1948.|$|R
